

# Reference : 
# http://www.ubuntubuzz.com/2016/09/how-to-create-deepin-153-gnulinux-bootable-usb.html

# lsblk shows a tree of drives from your computer
# Find your USB drive



# Open Terminal and run this dd command line:
sudo dd if=file.iso of=/dev/sdc bs=4M

# if: input file
# of: output file
# file.iso: change this name into your deepin iso file name
# /dev/sdc: change this address into the correct address of your USB drive


# Open a new Terminal and perform this command line:
sudo pkill -USR1 -x -n dd
